31/07/2008
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Two workers were crushed to death on Wednesday (July 30th) at a French-owned cement factory in eastern Romania.
Authorities say the two were repairing an industrial cement mixer.
The plant in Medgidia, near the Black Sea coast, belongs to the world's largest cement producer, Lafarge SA.
(Mediafax, Agerpres, Realitatea TV, AP - 30/07/08)
